data.title: Honeymoon Horror
data.meta_description: Honeymoon Horror is a single-stage overseer quest inÂ Fallout Shelter. This level is full of mole rats, sometimes with broodmothers, as well as radscorpions. There will also be a glowing radscorpion accompanied by another two regular radscorpions. Upon reaching the newlyweds, one can choose...
data.text:
Opening dialogue Dweller response Character response We're the rescue party, but we're not going any deeper with all the Radscorpions around!

After all, the food at the wedding was awful! Why risk our lives for them?

So we sent the cat ahead to find them and bring them back.

Now... why are you here again?

To do your job. So hand over those Stimpaks. Awesome, we're off the hook! Here you go. To do your job. Now give us your RadAway. You won't be needing them. Awesome, we're off the hook! Here you go. To do your job. And we'll be taking one of your Laser Rifles to help us out. Fine by us! Here you go. To do your job. But we'll keep quiet about your cowardice if you've got enough Caps. I guess that's fair. A good reputation isn't going to keep itself! We're saved! Thank you so much!

A nice cat kept us safe when those creatures attacked! But otherwise it just slept...

But please don't take us back to the settlement. It's horrible there!

The wedding gifts we got were so cheap! We can't imagine going back.

Would you please just shut up and go home already? You've caused enough trouble. Fine. But you're stuck with the ugly dress they gave me. A dusty Librarian Outfit? Really? Actually, there's room in my Vault for one more person. Patricia, you can come. Darling, I'll never forget you as I toil away in complete safety. Stay strong! You know... there's room in my Vault for one more person. Grant, you're invited. My husband would never aband... Oh, you want to go? Fine then. Go.
